# App version — single source of truth

## Automatic bump on deploy (Vercel)

Every production build runs `bump-version.mjs --ci` when `VERCEL=1` (see `build-frontend-prod.mjs`).
Message comes from the git commit. No manual bump needed per release.

Manual only when testing locally:
```bash
cd frontend && npm run bump-version -- "وصف التحديث"
```

## Files synced on bump

- `frontend/version.json` — `version` + `message`
- `frontend/js/modules/app-utils.js` → `AppState.appVersion` fallback
- `frontend/service-worker.js` → `CACHE_VERSION` (cache bust)

Skip: `SKIP_BUMP_VERSION=1`

## How updates are detected

- `saas-version.js` fetches `/version.json` (no-cache via vercel.json)
- Compares with `localStorage.hse_last_seen_version`
- Login footer + sidebar badge + banner/modal when server version is newer

## Example version.json

```json
{
  "version": "2.2.14",
  "message": "تحسين تصميم إعدادات النماذج"
}
```
